431. Rev Urol. 2003;5 Suppl 1(Suppl 1):S11-5.

Development of an index to evaluate symptoms in men with androgen deficiency.

O'leary MP.

Healthier lifestyles and better medical care are contributing to greater life 
expectancy in U.S. males. Couple this with the great emphasis our society places 
on youth, and it is not surprising that older men want to look, feel, and act 
younger. Androgen replacement may have a role in this setting, but it is not 
clear exactly what symptoms signal a problem or warrant therapy. A valid and 
reproducible index that sufficiently defines the problems experienced by 
androgen-deficient men will go a long way toward helping both researchers and 
clinicians better understand and manage these men.

